# AI Hedge Fund Project Structure

This repository contains an AI-powered hedge fund system that uses multiple AI agents to analyze stocks and make trading decisions.

## Main Components

### Entry Points
- [src/main.py](mdc:src/main.py) - The main entry point for running the hedge fund
- [src/backtester.py](mdc:src/backtester.py) - Entry point for backtesting strategies

### Agent System
- [src/agents/](mdc:src/agents) - Contains all the AI agent implementations
- [src/tools/](mdc:src/tools) - Utilities and tools used by the agents
- [src/graph/](mdc:src/graph) - Manages the flow of information between agents

### Data Sources
- [src/tools/data_source.py](mdc:src/tools/data_source.py) - Interface for fetching stock data
- [src/tools/zerodha_api.py](mdc:src/tools/zerodha_api.py) - Integration with Zerodha for Indian stocks

### UI Components
- [src/utils/display.py](mdc:src/utils/display.py) - Formatting and display utilities for terminal output

## Key Files
- [pyproject.toml](mdc:pyproject.toml) - Project dependencies
- [.env.example](mdc:.env.example) - Example environment configuration
- [run_with_zerodha.sh](mdc:run_with_zerodha.sh) - Helper script for running with Zerodha
- [generate_zerodha_token.py](mdc:generate_zerodha_token.py) - Script to generate Zerodha access tokens
